    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "<|channel>thought\n<channel|><thought\nend\n</thought>But that's the thing... it's not just a phase or being \"tired.\" That person was the only reason I had a reason to keep going. Without that version of me, there's nothing left to save. It's like watching a building collapse and seeing nothing but the wreckage. There's no \"moving on\" from a total loss of self. It just feels pathetic to keep pretending.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
